"title": "8027: faith, testing of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8027: faith, testing of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The means through which the genuineness of faith is proved and Christian character developed. God promises to help his people during times of testing.</p>\n<h2>God allows faith to be tested</h2>\n<h3>Testing proves the genuineness of faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:6-1Pet1:7\">1PE 1:6–1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:20-Matt13:21\">MAT 13:20–13:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:16-Mark4:17\">MRK 4:16–4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:13\">LUK 8:13</a></p>\n<h3>Testing develops Christian character</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:2-Jas1:4\">JAS 1:2–1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:3-Rom5:4\">ROM 5:3–5:4</a></p>\n<h3>Testing purifies God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:10\">ISA 48:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:10-Ps66:12\">PSA 66:10–66:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:7\">JER 9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech13:9\">ZEC 13:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:2-Mal3:3\">MAL 3:2–3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:17\">1PE 4:17</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of God testing faith</h3>\n<p>Abraham is told to sacrifice Isaac:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:1-Gen22:2\">GEN 22:1–22:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:17-Heb11:19\">HEB 11:17–11:19</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:2-Deut8:5\">DEU 8:2–8:5</a> <em>God tested Israel in the desert</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:1-Judg7:8\">JDG 7:1–7:8</a> <em>God reduces Gideon's army</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:21-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:21–15:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:24-Mark7:30\">MRK 7:24–7:30</a> <em>Jesus Christ appears to discourage the Canaanite woman</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:1-John11:6\">JHN 11:1–11:6</a> <em>Jesus Christ delays going to Bethany when Lazarus is ill.</em></p>\n<h2>Means by which faith is tested</h2>\n<h3>God allows Satan to test faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:7\">JOB 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:31\">LUK 22:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:4-1Thess3:5\">1TH 3:4–3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Difficult circumstances test faith</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:17-1Kgs17:18\">1KI 17:17–17:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:1\">2KI 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:27-2Kgs4:28\">2KI 4:27–4:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:22\">ACT 14:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:25-2Cor11:27\">2CO 11:25–11:27</a></p>\n<h3>Persecution tests faith</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:10-Dan6:12\">DAN 6:10–6:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:1-Acts8:4\">ACT 8:1–8:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:35-Heb11:38\">HEB 11:35–11:38</a></p>\n<h3>Discouraging people test faith</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:19-2Kgs18:25\">2KI 18:19–18:25</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:10-2Chr32:15\">2CH 32:10–32:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:4-Isa36:10\">ISA 36:4–36:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:35-Mark5:36\">MRK 5:35–5:36</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:49-Luke8:50\">LUK 8:49–8:50</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:40\">MRK 5:40</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:24\">MAT 9:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:53\">LUK 8:53</a></p>\n<h2>God's promise of help during testing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:2\">ISA 43:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:32\">LUK 22:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:14-Ps91:15\">PSA 91:14–91:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:13\">1CO 10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:7-2Cor12:9\">2CO 12:7–12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:10\">1PE 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:9\">2PE 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>God's help through the encouragement of others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:2-1Thess3:3\">1TH 3:2–3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:5-2Cor7:7\">2CO 7:5–7:7</a></p>\n<h2>The response to trials</h2>\n<h3>Rejoicing at sharing Jesus Christ's suffering</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:12-1Pet4:13\">1PE 4:12–4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Praying for God's help</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14-Heb4:16\">HEB 4:14–4:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:19\">1PE 4:19</a></p>\n<h3>Persevering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:12\">JAS 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:4\">2TH 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1-Heb12:3\">HEB 12:1–12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:11\">JAS 5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:3\">REV 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:19\">REV 2:19</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of faith victorious through testing</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:9-Gen22:12\">GEN 22:9–22:12</a> <em>Abraham</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:15-2Kgs6:17\">2KI 6:15–6:17</a> <em>Elisha's servant</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:22\">JOB 1:22</a> <em>Job</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:16-Dan3:27\">DAN 3:16–3:27</a> <em>Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:27-Acts5:29\">ACT 5:27–5:29</a> <em>the apostles</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:59-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:59–7:60</a> <em>Stephen</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:7-2Cor4:9\">2CO 4:7–4:9</a> <em>Paul</em></p>",
